      "*": "{{Chapter Box\n| title = To Arabasta\n| image = \n| jname = アラバスタへ\n| rname = Arabasuta e\n| ename = On to Alabasta\n}}\n\n'''Chapter 154''' is titled \"To Arabasta\".\n\n==Cover Page==\n[[Jango's Dance Paradise]], Vol. 22: \"The Power of a Marine Headquarters Lieutenant\".\n\n[[Fullbody]] goes into action, crushing the [[Tulip Pirates]] almost singlehandedly.\n\n==Short Summary==\nWhile [[Kureha]] and [[Dalton]] rejoice about the now possible rebirth of their country, they learn that [[Tony Tony Chopper|Chopper]] has joined a group of pirates whose captain is worth {{B}}30,000,000. Meanwhile, Chopper discovers the life on board the [[Going Merry]] with his new friends.\n\n==Long Summary==\n[[Kureha]] and Dalton are sitting under the sakura snow, now full of hope about the future of their country when a villager appears carrying [[Monkey D. Luffy|Luffy]]'s bounty poster. Understanding their friend has encountered some dangerous people, Kureha makes mysterious remarks about [[Gol D. Roger]] and the [[Will of D.]] When asked about where the poster came from, the villager replies that a few days ago, a stranger appeared, looking for the [[Blackbeard Pirates]] who destroyed the island. When the stranger called [[Portgas D. Ace|Ace]] learned that they have already left, he gave Luffy's poster to the villagers so that, in case he reaches [[Drum Island|Drum]], they can tell Luffy he would wait for him in [[Arabasta]] for 10 days.\n\nOnboard the [[Going Merry]], Chopper is full of nostalgia and does not rejoice with the others, who are having a sakura party. However, once [[Nami]] gives him his medicine bag, which he had no time to prepare during his hasty departure, he understands that Kureha did it for him, secretly agreeing with his departure. This revelation changes his mood and he quickly learns the crew's customs who happily celebrate the new Straw Hats' doctor.\n\nMeanwhile in [[Little Garden]], an [[okama]] named [[Bentham|Mr. 2]] is searching for [[Galdino|Mr. 3]] in order to accomplish [[Crocodile]]'s orders to kill him, but Mr. 3 is nowhere to be found.\n\n==Quick Reference==\n===Chapter Notes===\n*Dr. [[Kureha]] mentions the [[Will of D.]] for the first time.\n*Gold Roger's real name was [[Gol D. Roger]].\n*A few days ago, a stranger named [[Portgas D. Ace|Ace]] arrived on [[Drum Island]] on a day when it did not snow.\n**Ace told the citizens to tell [[Monkey D. Luffy|Luffy]] that he will be waiting in [[Arabasta]] for ten days.\n**Ace is also looking for the [[Blackbeard Pirates]].\n*[[Bentham|Mr. 2]] is fully seen for the first time\n*[[Crocodile]] decides to head into Alabasta to show his position as the kingdom's hero.\n*This is the last chapter of the [[Drum Island Arc]].\n\n===Characters===\n{| class=\"CharTable\"\n! [[Pirate]]s\n! [[Marines]]\n! Citizens\n! [[Baroque Works]]\n! Others\n|-\n|\n;[[Straw Hat Pirates]]\n*[[Monkey D. Luffy]]\n*[[Roronoa Zoro]]\n*[[Nami]]\n*[[Usopp]]\n*[[Sanji]]\n*[[Tony Tony Chopper]]\n|\n;[[Marine Ranks#Lieutenant|Lieutenant]]\n*[[Fullbody]] (cover)\n|\n;[[Drum Island]]\n*[[Dalton]]\n*[[Kureha]]\n----\n;[[Arabasta]]\n*[[Nefertari Vivi]]\n*[[Karoo]]\n|\n*[[Crocodile]]\n*[[Nico Robin|Miss All Sunday]]\n----\n;[[Baroque Works#Members|Officer Agents]]\n*[[Bentham|Mr. 2 Bon Kurei]]\n----\n;[[Baroque Works#Billions|Billions]]\n*[[Akumai]]\n|\n*[[Portgas D. Ace|Ace]] (flashback)\n|}\n\n==Author Comment==\n{{WSJ Comment}}\n\n==Site Navigation==\n{{Drum Island Arc}}\n{{Jango's Dance Paradise}}\n[[ca:Capítol 154]]\n[[it:Capitolo 154]]"
